In[5]:
mu = sp500['returns'].mean()         # average daily return
sigma = sp500['returns'].std()       # daily volatility
last_price = sp500[('Close', '^GSPC')].iloc[-1]  # latest S&P 500 price
In[6]:
num_simulations = 1000
num_days = 252  # 1 trading year
In[7]:
simulations = np.zeros((num_days, num_simulations))

for i in range(num_simulations):
    prices = [last_price]
    for _ in range(num_days - 1):
        price = prices[-1] * np.exp((mu - 0.5 * sigma**2) + sigma * np.random.normal())
        prices.append(price)
    simulations[:, i] = prices
In[8]:
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(simulations)
plt.title('Monte Carlo Simulation of S&P 500')
plt.xlabel('Days')
plt.ylabel('Index Value')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

In[14]:
#Now I want to do it based on monthly data and project the next 5 years
sp500_monthly = sp500.resample('M').last()  
sp500_monthly['returns'] = sp500_monthly[('Close', '^GSPC')].pct_change()
mu_monthly = sp500_monthly['returns'].mean()
sigma_monthly = sp500_monthly['returns'].std()
last_price_monthly = sp500_monthly[('Close', '^GSPC')].iloc[-1]  # latest S&P 500 price
num_months = 60  # 5 years
simulations_monthly = np.zeros((num_months, num_simulations))
for i in range(num_simulations):
    prices = [last_price_monthly]
    for _ in range(num_months - 1):
        price = prices[-1] * np.exp((mu_monthly - 0.5 * sigma_monthly**2) + sigma_monthly * np.random.normal())
        prices.append(price)
    simulations_monthly[:, i] = prices
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(simulations_monthly)
plt.title('Monte Carlo Simulation of S&P 500 (Monthly)')
plt.xlabel('Months')
plt.ylabel('Index Value')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

# now I want to do it based on the Nasdaq
nasdaq = yf.download('^IXIC', start='2018-01-01', end='2024-12-31')
num_simulations_nasdaq = num_simulations  # use the same number as S&P 500
num_months_nasdaq = 60  # 5 years
nasdaq_monthly = nasdaq.resample('M').last()
nasdaq_monthly['returns'] = nasdaq_monthly[('Close', '^IXIC')].pct_change()
mu_nasdaq_monthly = nasdaq_monthly['returns'].mean()
sigma_nasdaq_monthly = nasdaq_monthly['returns'].std()
last_price_nasdaq_monthly = nasdaq_monthly[('Close', '^IXIC')].iloc[-1]
simulations_nasdaq_monthly = np.zeros((num_months_nasdaq, num_simulations_nasdaq))
for i in range(num_simulations_nasdaq):
    prices = [last_price_nasdaq_monthly]
    for _ in range(num_months_nasdaq - 1):
        price = prices[-1] * np.exp((mu_nasdaq_monthly - 0.5 * sigma_nasdaq_monthly**2) + sigma_nasdaq_monthly * np.random.normal())
        prices.append(price)
    simulations_nasdaq_monthly[:, i] = prices
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(simulations_nasdaq_monthly)
plt.title('Monte Carlo Simulation of Nasdaq (Monthly)')
plt.xlabel('Months')
plt.ylabel('Index Value')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

In[25]:
sp500 = yf.download('^GSPC', start='2004-01-01', end='2024-12-31')
nasdaq = yf.download('^IXIC', start='2004-01-01', end='2024-12-31')
# Resample to monthly data for both indices
sp500_monthly = sp500.resample('M').last()
sp500_monthly['returns'] = sp500_monthly[('Close', '^GSPC')].pct_change()
mu_monthly = sp500_monthly['returns'].mean()
sigma_monthly = sp500_monthly['returns'].std()
last_price_monthly = sp500_monthly[('Close', '^GSPC')].iloc[-1]

nasdaq_monthly = nasdaq.resample('M').last()
nasdaq_monthly['returns'] = nasdaq_monthly[('Close', '^IXIC')].pct_change()
mu_nasdaq_monthly = nasdaq_monthly['returns'].mean()
sigma_nasdaq_monthly = nasdaq_monthly['returns'].std()
last_price_nasdaq_monthly = nasdaq_monthly[('Close', '^IXIC')].iloc[-1]

num_months = 60  # 5 years
num_simulations = 1000

# S&P 500 simulations
simulations_monthly = np.zeros((num_months, num_simulations))
for i in range(num_simulations):
    prices = [last_price_monthly]
    for _ in range(num_months - 1):
        price = prices[-1] * np.exp((mu_monthly - 0.5 * sigma_monthly**2) + sigma_monthly * np.random.normal())
        prices.append(price)
    simulations_monthly[:, i] = prices

# Nasdaq simulations
simulations_nasdaq_monthly = np.zeros((num_months, num_simulations))
for i in range(num_simulations):
    prices = [last_price_nasdaq_monthly]
    for _ in range(num_months - 1):
        price = prices[-1] * np.exp((mu_nasdaq_monthly - 0.5 * sigma_nasdaq_monthly**2) + sigma_nasdaq_monthly * np.random.normal())
        prices.append(price)
    simulations_nasdaq_monthly[:, i] = prices
